1. What is HTML, and what is its role in web development?
HTML (HyperText Markup Language) was created by Tim Berners-Lee in 1991 as a standard for creating web pages.
It is a scripting language used to design static web pages.
H- Hyper refers to the reference link.
T- text refers to the date/information.
M- markup refers to adding predefined tags and attributes to define elements.
L- language refers to a system of communication or instruction understood by both humans and computers.
Think of html as the building blocks that create the structure and look of a website, similar to how bricks and mortar are used to build a house.
In a nutshell:
1.HTML is the language of the web, used to create websites.
2.HTML defines the barebone structure or layout of web pages that we see on the Internet.
3.HTML consists of a set of tags contained within an HTML document, and the associated files typically have either a ".html" or ".htm" extension.


2. What is web development?
Web development refers to the process of creating, building, and maintaining websites or web applications that are accessible via the internet or an intranet. I
Web development is like building a house on the internet. instead of bricks and mortar, we use code to create websites and web applications. Think of it as designing and putting together all the parts of a webpage, like pictures, text, buttons, and forms, so that when you visit a website, everything looks nice and works smoothly.


3. What are the core technologies used in web development?
 HTML, CSS, and JavaScript are the main three technologies you'll use to build a website.
 HTML- It defines the structure and layout of web page.
 CSS- It is used for styling the web pages.
 JS- It adds interactivity and dynamic behaviour.

4. What is CSS and what is its purpose?
 CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets. It is a style sheet language used to define the presentation and layout of HTML documents, including colors, fonts, spacing, and positioning of elements on a web page.
 Its main purpose is to control how things appear on a webpage. For example, it decides what color the text should be, how big the headings are, how much space there is around images.
 CSS helps ensure that websites look consistent and attractive across different devices, like computers, tablets, and phones. 


 5. What are the basic data types in JavaScrip?
 JavaScript has 8 Datatypes
 1. String- Represents textual data enclosed in single quotes (') or double quotes (").
 2. Number- Represents numeric values, including integers and floating-point numbers. 
 3. Bigint-  allows you to work with really big whole numbers.
 4. Boolean- Represents a logical value that can be either true or false.
 5. Undefined- Represents a variable that has been declared but not assigned a value.
 6. Null - Represents an empty value or has no value.
 7. Symbol- Represents a unique and immutable value that may be used as the key of an object property.
 8. Object- Represents a collection of key-value pairs where keys are strings (or Symbols) and values can be any data type, including other objects.
 